This is a complete kit to transform your Glock 23 or 32 to 9MM or to add a stainless steel ported barrel to your Glock 19. It also includes a Glock 17 (Genuine) magazine with a Pearce +2 magazine extension and an A&G grip extender (to fill the gap).

I used the set-up for two purposes. The first was to shoot cheaper (and more available) 9MM ammo out of my Glock 32 (.357 Sig). The second was to use my Glock for tactical drills and speed shooting. I've since moved on to a 1911 and this kit has been collecting dust in my safe.

The first reason is probably pretty obvious. 9MM ammo is about $15/box cheaper than .357 Sig and about $6/box cheaper than .40 S&W. What you may not realize is that the ported barrel has a pretty dramatic effect on felt recoil and muzzle flip from the 9MM round. It also adds about another 1/2" to the barrel, increasing accuracy. That makes it great for speed shooting and tactical drills and the 19 round capacity of the extended magazine will have to out in the field for a while before needing to reload.

I used this set-up on a Gen 3 Glock 32. I'm unsure as to how it would function on a Gen 4. You're welcome to install it and try it out to ensure it will function. It performed flawlessly on mine with 115gr loads. I did not have to change the stock spring.

This barrel will not work on a full size Glock (17/22/31). I'm unsure as to whether or not it will function on a sub-compact (26/27/33). My gut says it will not, but again, you're welcome to try.

I'm open to hearing what you have for trade (including me or you adding boot), but I'm mainly interested in cash. My Glock 32 is not for sale.

If you want to check it out, e-mail me through Armslist or call/text me @ REDACTED. My name is Justin and I've been a permit holder since 2007. Thanks.
